{{#if (eq project.language "pt-BR")}}
# Regra #11 — Delegacao Paralela

## Problema

Delegacao sequencial desperica 2-4x tempo. Se `database`, `backend` e `frontend` sao delegados um apos o outro — e `backend` nao depende de `frontend` — o tempo total e a soma de todos. Com ondas paralelas, o tempo total e o da onda mais lenta.

## Grafo de Dependencias

```
database
  ├──→ backend
  │      ├──→ frontend
  │      └──→ mobile
  └──→ agent-ai
           └──→ backend (feedback loop)

e2e ← depende de TODOS (executa por ultimo)
```

**Regra geral**: Camadas inferiores primeiro. Camadas independentes em paralelo.

### Dependencias por Role

| Role | Depende de | Dependido por |
|------|-----------|---------------|
{{#each modules}}
{{#if (eq role "database")}}
| {{name}} (database) | — | backend, agent-ai |
{{else if (eq role "backend")}}
| {{name}} (backend) | database | frontend, mobile |
{{else if (eq role "agent-ai")}}
| {{name}} (agent-ai) | database | backend (feedback) |
{{else if (eq role "frontend")}}
| {{name}} (frontend) | backend | e2e |
{{else if (eq role "mobile")}}
| {{name}} (mobile) | backend | e2e |
{{else if (eq role "e2e")}}
| {{name}} (e2e) | todos | — |
{{else}}
| {{name}} ({{role}}) | conforme definido | conforme definido |
{{/if}}
{{/each}}

## Algoritmo: Ondas Paralelas

```
1. LISTAR todas as tarefas pendentes
2. CONSULTAR grafo de dependencias
3. AGRUPAR em ondas:
   - Onda N: tarefas cujas dependencias JA foram concluidas
4. Para cada onda:
   a. LANCAR delegates em paralelo (multiplas chamadas Agent)
   b. AGUARDAR todos os delegates da onda
   c. VALIDAR resultados (spec-validate por delegate)
   d. Se algum FALHOU → tratar falha parcial (ver abaixo)
5. AVANCAR para proxima onda
6. CONSOLIDAR resultado final
```

## Exemplo: Feature com 4 Modulos

**Tarefas**: migration (database), endpoint (backend), tela (frontend), cenario (e2e)

```
Onda 1: [ database ]              ← sem dependencias
Onda 2: [ backend, agent-ai ]     ← dependem de database
Onda 3: [ frontend, mobile ]      ← dependem de backend
Onda 4: [ e2e ]                   ← depende de todos
```

**Tempo sequencial**: ~20 min (5+5+5+5)
**Tempo paralelo**: ~12 min (5+5+2+5, ondas 2 e 3 em paralelo internamente)

## Exemplo: Feature com 2 Modulos Independentes

**Tarefas**: componente (frontend), endpoint (backend) — sem dependencia mutua

```
Onda 1: [ frontend, backend ]     ← paralelo total
Onda 2: [ e2e ]                   ← apos ambos
```

{{#ifRule "tdd-sequential-enforcement"}}
## TDD em Paralelo (Regra #9)

O ciclo Red-Green DEVE respeitar a Regra #9, mas ondas paralelas sao permitidas **entre modulos diferentes**:

```
Onda 1 (Red):   [ database-tests, backend-tests ]    ← paralelo entre modulos
Onda 2 (Green): [ database-impl, backend-impl ]      ← paralelo entre modulos
Onda 3 (Red):   [ frontend-tests, mobile-tests ]     ← paralelo entre modulos
Onda 4 (Green): [ frontend-impl, mobile-impl ]       ← paralelo entre modulos
```

**REGRA ABSOLUTA**: Dentro do MESMO modulo, Red e Green sao SEMPRE sequenciais.

| Cenario | Permitido? |
|---------|-----------|
| Red(backend) ∥ Red(frontend) | SIM — modulos diferentes |
| Green(backend) ∥ Green(frontend) | SIM — modulos diferentes |
| Red(backend) ∥ Green(backend) | NAO — mesmo modulo, Regra #9 |
| Red(backend) → Green(backend) | SIM — sequencial no mesmo modulo |
{{/ifRule}}

## Tratamento de Falha Parcial

Quando um delegate falha em uma onda, os demais da mesma onda **continuam**:

| Cenario | Acao |
|---------|------|
| 1 delegate falha, outros OK | Registrar falha, continuar com proxima onda (pular dependentes do falhado) |
| Todos falham na onda | Parar execucao, reportar ao usuario |
| Falha em modulo sem dependentes | Registrar, continuar normalmente |
| Falha em modulo com dependentes | Registrar, pular dependentes, continuar independentes |
| Falha intermitente (timeout) | Retry 1x. Se falhar novamente → registrar e pular |

**NUNCA** parar toda a execucao por falha de um unico delegate (exceto se todos falharam).

{{#ifRule "execution-trace"}}
## Integracao com Trace (Regra #10)

Cada onda DEVE ser registrada no trace file:

```markdown
### Onda 2 — Paralela
- **Delegates**: backend, agent-ai
- **Inicio**: {timestamp}

#### backend
- Status: PASS
- Arquivos: [lista]
- Spec-Validate: PASS

#### agent-ai
- Status: FAIL → retry → PASS
- Arquivos: [lista]
- Spec-Validate: PASS (apos retry)

- **Fim**: {timestamp}
- **Duracao**: {tempo}
```
{{/ifRule}}

## Tabela de Estrategias

| # | Cenario | Estrategia | Ondas |
|---|---------|-----------|-------|
| 1 | Feature full-stack (DB+API+UI) | Sequencial por camada | DB → API → UI → E2E |
| 2 | Feature backend + frontend sem dep | Paralelo total | [API, UI] → E2E |
| 3 | Feature somente backend | Sequencial simples | DB → API |
| 4 | Feature somente frontend | Delegate unico | UI |
| 5 | Bug fix multi-modulo | Paralelo se independentes | [mod-A, mod-B] |
| 6 | Refactoring transversal | Sequencial (risco alto) | mod-1 → mod-2 → mod-3 |
| 7 | Feature com agent-ai | DB primeiro, depois paralelo | DB → [API, AI] → UI |

## Relacao com Outras Regras

{{#ifRule "delegation-protocol"}}
- **Regra #0 (Delegacao)**: Ondas paralelas seguem o mesmo protocolo de prompt e contrato de resposta
{{/ifRule}}
{{#ifRule "tdd-sequential-enforcement"}}
- **Regra #9 (TDD Sequential)**: Red/Green sequencial dentro do modulo, paralelo entre modulos
{{/ifRule}}
{{#ifRule "execution-trace"}}
- **Regra #10 (Trace)**: Cada onda e registrada como bloco no trace file
{{/ifRule}}

## Violacao

| Situacao | Severidade | Consequencia |
|----------|-----------|--------------|
| Tarefas independentes executadas sequencialmente | **WARNING** | Anti-pattern, nao bloqueante — refazer com ondas |
| Dependente lancado antes da dependencia | **BLOQUEIO** | Parar e reordenar |
| Red+Green paralelos no mesmo modulo | **BLOQUEIO** | Viola Regra #9 |
| Falha parcial para toda a execucao | **WARNING** | Continuar independentes, nao parar tudo |
{{else}}
# Rule #11 — Parallel Delegation

## Problem

Sequential delegation wastes 2-4x time. If `database`, `backend`, and `frontend` are delegated one after another — and `backend` doesn't depend on `frontend` — total time is the sum of all. With parallel waves, total time is that of the slowest wave.

## Dependency Graph

```
database
  ├──→ backend
  │      ├──→ frontend
  │      └──→ mobile
  └──→ agent-ai
           └──→ backend (feedback loop)

e2e ← depends on ALL (executes last)
```

**General rule**: Lower layers first. Independent layers in parallel.

### Dependencies by Role

| Role | Depends on | Depended by |
|------|-----------|-------------|
{{#each modules}}
{{#if (eq role "database")}}
| {{name}} (database) | — | backend, agent-ai |
{{else if (eq role "backend")}}
| {{name}} (backend) | database | frontend, mobile |
{{else if (eq role "agent-ai")}}
| {{name}} (agent-ai) | database | backend (feedback) |
{{else if (eq role "frontend")}}
| {{name}} (frontend) | backend | e2e |
{{else if (eq role "mobile")}}
| {{name}} (mobile) | backend | e2e |
{{else if (eq role "e2e")}}
| {{name}} (e2e) | all | — |
{{else}}
| {{name}} ({{role}}) | as defined | as defined |
{{/if}}
{{/each}}

## Algorithm: Parallel Waves

```
1. LIST all pending tasks
2. CONSULT dependency graph
3. GROUP into waves:
   - Wave N: tasks whose dependencies have ALREADY been completed
4. For each wave:
   a. LAUNCH delegates in parallel (multiple Agent calls)
   b. AWAIT all delegates in the wave
   c. VALIDATE results (spec-validate per delegate)
   d. If any FAILED → handle partial failure (see below)
5. ADVANCE to next wave
6. CONSOLIDATE final result
```

## Example: Feature with 4 Modules

**Tasks**: migration (database), endpoint (backend), screen (frontend), scenario (e2e)

```
Wave 1: [ database ]              ← no dependencies
Wave 2: [ backend, agent-ai ]     ← depend on database
Wave 3: [ frontend, mobile ]      ← depend on backend
Wave 4: [ e2e ]                   ← depends on all
```

**Sequential time**: ~20 min (5+5+5+5)
**Parallel time**: ~12 min (5+5+2+5, waves 2 and 3 parallel internally)

## Example: Feature with 2 Independent Modules

**Tasks**: component (frontend), endpoint (backend) — no mutual dependency

```
Wave 1: [ frontend, backend ]     ← fully parallel
Wave 2: [ e2e ]                   ← after both
```

{{#ifRule "tdd-sequential-enforcement"}}
## TDD in Parallel (Rule #9)

The Red-Green cycle MUST respect Rule #9, but parallel waves are allowed **between different modules**:

```
Wave 1 (Red):   [ database-tests, backend-tests ]    ← parallel across modules
Wave 2 (Green): [ database-impl, backend-impl ]      ← parallel across modules
Wave 3 (Red):   [ frontend-tests, mobile-tests ]     ← parallel across modules
Wave 4 (Green): [ frontend-impl, mobile-impl ]       ← parallel across modules
```

**ABSOLUTE RULE**: Within the SAME module, Red and Green are ALWAYS sequential.

| Scenario | Allowed? |
|----------|----------|
| Red(backend) ∥ Red(frontend) | YES — different modules |
| Green(backend) ∥ Green(frontend) | YES — different modules |
| Red(backend) ∥ Green(backend) | NO — same module, Rule #9 |
| Red(backend) → Green(backend) | YES — sequential in same module |
{{/ifRule}}

## Partial Failure Handling

When a delegate fails in a wave, the others in the same wave **continue**:

| Scenario | Action |
|----------|--------|
| 1 delegate fails, others OK | Record failure, continue with next wave (skip dependents of failed) |
| All fail in wave | Stop execution, report to user |
| Failure in module with no dependents | Record, continue normally |
| Failure in module with dependents | Record, skip dependents, continue independents |
| Intermittent failure (timeout) | Retry 1x. If fails again → record and skip |

**NEVER** stop the entire execution due to a single delegate failure (unless all failed).

{{#ifRule "execution-trace"}}
## Trace Integration (Rule #10)

Each wave MUST be recorded in the trace file:

```markdown
### Wave 2 — Parallel
- **Delegates**: backend, agent-ai
- **Start**: {timestamp}

#### backend
- Status: PASS
- Files: [list]
- Spec-Validate: PASS

#### agent-ai
- Status: FAIL → retry → PASS
- Files: [list]
- Spec-Validate: PASS (after retry)

- **End**: {timestamp}
- **Duration**: {time}
```
{{/ifRule}}

## Strategy Table

| # | Scenario | Strategy | Waves |
|---|----------|----------|-------|
| 1 | Full-stack feature (DB+API+UI) | Sequential by layer | DB → API → UI → E2E |
| 2 | Backend + frontend no dep | Fully parallel | [API, UI] → E2E |
| 3 | Backend-only feature | Simple sequential | DB → API |
| 4 | Frontend-only feature | Single delegate | UI |
| 5 | Multi-module bug fix | Parallel if independent | [mod-A, mod-B] |
| 6 | Cross-cutting refactoring | Sequential (high risk) | mod-1 → mod-2 → mod-3 |
| 7 | Feature with agent-ai | DB first, then parallel | DB → [API, AI] → UI |

## Relation to Other Rules

{{#ifRule "delegation-protocol"}}
- **Rule #0 (Delegation)**: Parallel waves follow the same prompt protocol and response contract
{{/ifRule}}
{{#ifRule "tdd-sequential-enforcement"}}
- **Rule #9 (TDD Sequential)**: Red/Green sequential within module, parallel across modules
{{/ifRule}}
{{#ifRule "execution-trace"}}
- **Rule #10 (Trace)**: Each wave is recorded as a block in the trace file
{{/ifRule}}

## Violation

| Situation | Severity | Consequence |
|-----------|----------|-------------|
| Independent tasks executed sequentially | **WARNING** | Anti-pattern, not blocking — redo with waves |
| Dependent launched before dependency | **BLOCK** | Stop and reorder |
| Red+Green parallel in same module | **BLOCK** | Violates Rule #9 |
| Partial failure stops all execution | **WARNING** | Continue independents, don't stop everything |
{{/if}}
